# {{name}}

Synoema project. Files: `.sno`. Entry point: `src/main.sno`.

## Commands

```
synoema run src/main.sno        -- interpret
synoema jit src/main.sno        -- JIT-compile (native speed)
synoema test tests/              -- run tests
synoema doc src/                 -- generate docs
synoema fmt src/                 -- format code
synoema --errors json run src/main.sno  -- JSON errors for LLM
```

## Language Quick Reference

BPE-aligned functional language for LLM code generation.
All 33 operators = exactly 1 cl100k_base token. 46% fewer tokens than Python.

### Mental model: what NOT to write

| Instead of (Haskell/Python) | Write in Synoema | Why |
|------------------------------|------------------|-----|
| `if c then x else y` | `? c -> x : y` | 3 tokens, no keywords |
| `let x = e in body` | indented block: `x = e` then `body` | offside rule |
| `def f(x):` / `fn x ->` / `fun` | `f x = body` | no def keyword |
| `return x` | last expression = value | expression-oriented |
| `case x of` | multi-equation `f Con = ...` | — |
| `data T = A \| B` | `T = A \| B` | no `data` |
| `class` / `instance` | `trait` / `impl` | — |
| `import M` | `use M (f g)` or `use M (*)` | selective or wildcard |
| `[1, 2, 3]` | `[1 2 3]` | **no commas** |
| `x:xs` bare in pattern | `(x:xs)` | **parens required** |
| `s1 + s2` (strings) | `s1 ++ s2` | `+` = numbers only |
| `f"x={x}"` | `"x=${x}"` | `${}` interpolation |
| `// comment` | `-- comment` | — |

### Core axioms

- **No def keyword** — `name args = body`; patterns via multiple equations
- **Offside rule** — indentation defines blocks (2-space)
- **Expression-oriented** — last expr = result; no `return`
- **Immutable** — all bindings are immutable
- **Strict** — eager evaluation, left-to-right
- **Types inferred** — annotations optional

### Operators (precedence low -> high)

| Op | Meaning | Prec |
|----|---------|------|
| `<-` | bind (IO) | 1 |
| `\|>` | pipe | 2 |
| `\|\|` `&&` | logic | 3-4 |
| `==` `!=` `<` `>` `<=` `>=` | compare | 5-6 |
| `++` | concat | 7 |
| `+` `-` | add/sub | 8 |
| `*` `/` `%` | mul/div/mod | 9 |
| `**` | power | 9 |
| `>>` | compose | 10 |
| `.` | field access | 12 |
| juxtaposition | apply `f x` | 13 |

### Examples

```sno
-- functions & pattern matching
fac 0 = 1
fac n = n * fac (n - 1)

-- conditional
fizzbuzz n =
  ? n % 15 == 0 -> "FizzBuzz"
  : ? n % 3 == 0 -> "Fizz"
  : ? n % 5 == 0 -> "Buzz"
  : show n

-- local bindings
hyp a b =
  a2 = a * a
  b2 = b * b
  a2 + b2

-- lists (space-separated, no commas)
xs = [1 2 3 4 5]
evens = [x | x <- [1..20], x % 2 == 0]
result = [1..10] |> filter (\x -> x % 2 == 0) |> map (\x -> x * x)

-- records
pt = {x = 3, y = 4}
dist {x, y} = x * x + y * y
moved = {...pt, x = pt.x + 1}

-- ADTs
Shape = Circle Float | Rect Float Float
area (Circle r) = r * r
area (Rect w h) = w * h

-- type classes
trait Show a
  show : a -> String
impl Show Shape
  show (Circle r) = "Circle " ++ show r
  show (Rect w h) = show w ++ "x" ++ show h

-- modules
mod Math
  square x = x * x
use Math (square)

-- multi-file imports
import "lib.sno"
use Lib (helper)

-- IO
main = print "hello" ; print "world"

-- testing
test "fac base" = fac 0 == 1
```

